title: Liz Cheney
added: Cheney supported the [[2021 efforts to remove Donald Trump from office#Impeachment|impeachment]] of President Trump following the January 6, [[2021 storming of the Capitol]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=King |first1=Ledyard |title=Read the statement from GOP Rep. title: Liz Cheney
added: {{main|2020 United States House of Representatives election in Wyoming}}

Cheney defeated Blake Stanley in the Republican primary, receiving 73% of the vote, and faced Democrat Lynnette Grey Bull in the general election, which she won with 69% of the vote.<ref>{{cite web |title=Statewide Candidates Official Summary Wyoming General Election - November 3, 2020 |url=https://sos.wyo.gov/Elections/Docs/2020/Results/General/2020_General_Statewide_Candidates_Summary.pdf |website=Wyoming Secretary of State |access-date=November 11, 2020}}</ref>

title: Liz Cheney
added: Many in the [[House Republican Conference]] were angered by Cheney's vote to impeach, and on February 3, 2021 they held a closed-door secret ballot vote on whether to remove her from her position in the Republican House leadership. She held her position by a 145-61 vote, with one voting present.<ref>https://www.cnn.com/2021/02/03/politics/liz-cheney-house-republican-meeting/index.html</ref>
